reviews.text: We had a great time my family and I. The location is clean, modern, trendy. Staff is welcoming and keen to the details. We were helped by Shannon and she made our experience unforgettable. It was a great time. The food was good, the piece of meat was great and well seasoned , green beans were great as well. Portions were a decent size. For parking i would recommend to park at the whole food parking , its more convenient.

Very good menu selection. Several seafood and meat options. Nice verity of add ons too. Nice quiet setting. And I wish more restaurants would do mini desserts. All food ordered was fresh and tasty. Service, well, needed improvement. They seemed to be short on food runners, and we actually got served the wrong order. When our order did come it was missing a side order. Our waitress seemed off a little. She wasn’t very attentive and was absent most of our dinner. I’d definitely go back and would recommend this location.

Ate an early dinner/late lunch here with two hungry teenagers.  Everyone left full and satisfied.  We started with the Ahi Tuna Tartar and the Avocado Toast...unfortunately, I couldn't get a photo of the toast fast enough, it was that good!  Hubby had the Shrimp and Grits and everyone who tried it said it was the "winner" of the table!  I had the Cedar Plank Grilled Salmon and it was wonderfully smoky and perfectly cooked.  Daughter had the Pork Chop, which was equally divine!  Sea Scallops were well cooked and wonderfully translucent.  Don't skip out on dessert!  They are cute little portions to leave your sweet tooth satisfied without being over filling!

My first time visiting here for a late dinner & the food, service & ambiance were very nice! I got the sea scallops entree, with a side of street corn & the sangria flight. My hunny got the salmon entree, mac n cheese & the French wine flight. Portions were good and everything was well seasoned. We also tried a couple of the dessert shots.

Pretty good restaurant. One of the better place to celebrate any special occasions like birthdays or anniversaries. This place was really modern and clean. I ordered flatbreads with different toppings and grilled salmon with the side. Flatbreads were delicious! Crispy on the bottom and the top was soft and the toppings perfectly complement the bread. But the show of the night was the salmon dish. As soon as I tasted it, I could that tell that it was fresh and exceptionally cooked. Really loved that dish. Desserts were also outstanding! I picked three different kinds came in a shot glasses. I had a such great experience from this place and definitely will visit again. I highly recommend this restaurant.

This was my first year Celebrating my 6 years old son's birthday.  We love it. Our host was really dedicated to us. She helped the kids and she was taking care of everything. Thanks for that awesome day.

My experience at Chuck-E-Cheeses went extremely well when I was about 7 or 8 before the pandemic. I had so much fun. I might as well come back another day, because I have not been here for more than 5 or 6 years because I lost motivation from playing these awesome arcade games.

First and last Bday party here, my 5 year old had fun but every guest and my pockets did NOT. The $300+not worth it! Literally paying for a chair and bad service. Guest waited an hour and 15 for food, then had 45 min to eat food, sing and cut cake🤦‍♀️ And the show too! 3 kids didn’t show up and they were reluctant on taking them off the tab. I had to pay $13 for each of my guest to eat salad because they were starving! When I tried canceling the food the “manager” told me it was already made. The nerve of these people! No apologies, no drinks given for them being behind. Just took my money and kicked me out at exactly the time my party ended. Disappointed

I can't say this for all CEC locations, but this one in particular I will never visit again. It has nothing to do with the staff, rather the atmosphere.

Staff seem friendly based on interaction & observation factoring it was on a busy day (Saturday afternoon). However, the place smelled like armpits & weed, half the machines didn't work despite taking my credits and there are barely any machines/games. They could of added more games by reducing the size of the reserved area for big parties/groups, but that's just my opinion. Lastly, arcades typically have this colorful vibrant scenery, but this location had gray dull walls that gave bad vibes.

By no means am I expecting a D&B experience, but previous CEC experiences at other locations and in the far past tells me that the CEC I experienced as a kid isn't the same now. Oh, my kids and niece didn't have fun either (2, 5 and 7).

It's become so generic you'd never know it's chuck e cheese.  It's just a hot, noisy, crowded place with kid's games (some of which didn't work or work correctly).  Dave & BB Busters is so much better

First time here but for what everyone in my party order I can say it is a great place to eat. All food was tasty, with its own style. Pancakes are delicious fluffy and tasty. The chicken and waffles was really good with the really nice in home syrup mix they have. And the shakes are amazing. The hibiscus mango it is a combination different and refreshing.
Really like this place. Recommend the shrimps and grits.

I was recently staying in the area and visited here twice in one week. So that suggests it is pretty good.

It certainly looks the part and feels nostalgic.
The menu is what you expect and more. Healthy and modern dishes that are pretty good.
I enjoyed their milkshakes.

The service was the part that let me down slightly.
It was quite slow and I had to chase for a few items on both visits.

Wife and I generally come here for late-night breakfast after a work week. Among the appetizer choices, we recommend looking past the cheese fries, that might sound tempting, and going for the shrimp quesadilla. We've ordered the cheese fries a couple of times before, but neither the wife nor I are fans of the type of fries served, which are thin, short, and its typically cold when served. The burger is decent with a nice sized patty, but the bun felt too dry/stale; we did ask for medium, but it came out well done. The pancakes are very nice, eggs are good, but the sausage was not as great. Staff are friendly, courteous, and professional with every experience, but we do consistently have to hunt them down for refills of the water, napkins, condiments, to-go boxes, and checks :) Staff are always very nice about it though. The only area of discomfort I have is the tipping...it's a little much to have 20%, 22%, and 25% as the easy choice options...understandable, but I also don't agree with servers pressing 22% by default on the device before stepping away to let us sign, especially with the price of menu items. Overall, a good place for late night hangouts with friends.

The Silver Diner has taken the reigns and redefined the former rules and beliefs surrounding “Diner Culture.” While Breakfast Staples like the Lumberjack and Worlds greatest Milkshakes continue to grace the Menu, there are obvious healthful and wholesome options also emerging, not to mention an ample selection of tasty Vegan entrees!

I enjoyed a  casual dinner with friends and we were thrilled to discover we could also make it a Happy Hour (or a Happy Dinner?) but ordering a glass of bubbles and an Old Bay Bloody Mary! I didn’t realize the Diner also has a full liquor license!? Next time it’s going to be one of their delicious milkshakes with Vodka in it! Undoubtedly!  :)

Made last minute plans and decided to come to Silver Diner. Food was great but our server was even better! Emmanuel was great, courteous, and professional even though it was a Friday night and very busy, he came to check on us multiple times and our drinks were never empty!
Food arrived quickly and was delicious.
They have a nice variety of vegan options. I love that you can customize your own bowl. I have tried almost everything off of their menu, and you can't go wrong.

Cute lil spot inside of MOM’s market. I’m not much of a health conscious eater or one that cares for meat substitutes but my girlfriend loves this place so I thought I’d give it a shot. The cauliflower tacos were amazing (got them with salsa verde and vegan crema).

They also make their own juices that are pretty good. I’d like to see their menu expand!

Always a great vegan meal!!
Located inside MOMs Organic Market this place is fantastic.  The servers are very accommodating and friendly.
Easy to see the market from Randolph Road and has lots of parking.
The food is SSSOOO FRESH and delicious. I got the  Crowder bowl and asked not to have it steamed, dressing on the side.
I also got 2 juices, The Pink Lady, kombucha on the side and another with carrots, apples and ginger. SO FRESH and HEALTHY!!
Love that I can pick up a few groceries along with a great lunch.
Would have given it a 5 star but it is organic pricey. The small juice is $6.50 each and the bowl is $9.50. I asked for a few additonal things which cost $.75 extra per item. I will say the portions are big, my 5 year old and I shared the bowl.
HIGHLY RECOMMEND for foodies!! Especially vegan foodies.

Eat here about once a week. The meals are typically good however their brown rice never seems to be cooked correctly and unfortunately can ruin a meal. I’ve gotten it multiples time where it’s hard as a rock and feels like it going to crack my tooth. I’m not sure if it’s because it’s sitting all day but really hope they can get that sorted out because it’s ruined more than a few of the meals I’ve gotten from here.

Always great fresh vegetable meals. I haven't tried all of them but have been getting the cauliflower chickpea tacos recently. I'll buy a can of wild salmon and add it to it with a little extra kick from some of the sauces.

I ordered a free pizza and bought some bread. Worst bread I’ve ever bitten into. You could literally hear the oily crunch from down a hall. The bread was dry to the core literally. The pizza I was going to say it was good until my grandmother ended up finding hair inside the cheese. I’m making a complaint to corporate. Good luck

The world of pizza and value there is a te we're people will choose quality ingredients on a pizza vs low quality
On top of that 1.3 oz of ranch dressing cost $.75 plus tax it's more.like a rip off including a bad upsell the quality is truly on the lower end from all pizza stores I still rank out Ledo and Frank's to be the top pizza shops in area ..

Terrible customer service! Online order placed for Vegetarian pizza and pasta, but the store sent the wrong order with meat on the pizza and pasta! When we called the store, the person said they did not add any meat and that we can reorder the pizza! This is an absurd demand when they clearly made the mistake!! I have always ordered pizza from this place but probably the New staff does not care about their customers

Its a clean and professional location! I'd definitely call in ahead. I ordered in person and sat waiting. One of their teammates even reminded the crew I was waiting for food before heading out and they still forgot to let me know my food was ready. That tracker on the monitor really helped me out seeing when my order was done!

Bad food and even worse customer service.
I got a pizza today that was messed up so called to exchange it for an edible one.  Instead of simply replacing it, the manager immediately started arguing with me.  He told me that he made it "perfect" so too bad and if I want a new one, I'd have to pay for it again.  😂
After reading through the reviews, it seems his attitude and cheapness are well known around there because I saw other people that had the exact same story as me.  No wonder the place has gone down hill! I definitely won't be returning (not that they wanted my business anyhow it seems).  I Highly recommend &pizza that's only 1 mile away.

It was a busy Sunday evening. We were greeted and sat down at the booth. The complementary chips and salsa was a good start. The Signature Whiskey Glazed Sampler was very tasteful - crispy shrimp were fresh, sesame chicken were delicious, and the ribs are juicy. Onion soup might need more cheese. House salad was healthy. Kids meals did not have any vegetables, so just pasta and mashed potatoes.

Great TGI location! Delicious food and great service!

Pros:
Yummy burgers
Tasty fries
Fast service
Friendly employees
Everything Clean
Plenty of tables
Plenty of parking
Free parking

No stupid masks
No stupid vaccine passports

Just great food, great service and good times!

Look, I don't mind waiting...but holy Christmas.  40 min for a drink! I had to pick food up for lunch. Our orders sat in the pick up bins, drinks not put in cups yet. Had a hostess, waiter, cook,  and manager all stare at the order stapled to the bag. They looked at me, each one asking me the same question,  then just leave. I used to love coming here during my college years. Great atmosphere. What happened? Maybe I should come in inebriated so I won't care so much either.

I came here to try the $5 for 10 wings Monday's, I was disappointed, the chicken was overcooked and super chewy, the garlic parmasean sauce was pretty tasty.

I've always loved the burgers here since they are seasoned. The macaroni and cheese is pretty good too along with the fries!

I was double charge and manager Luis was rude!!! I expect my money back,,the bill was $230.46, we gave $220 cash and ask to put the rest on my card, waitress charge an extra $110.46 on my card; Luis came back and told us it takes 8 days to get it back and didn’t gives us a refund receipt and didn’t apologize.

WORST customer service!!!! There are only two employees. Only one that seems to be in charge has good service. The other employee actually rolled her eyes and throw sandwich when she mistakenly toasted my bread. She never asked, she just assumed I want it toasted. I asked her if there's a problem then she rolled her eyes again. It's ashame that I used to go to this subway and was going to continue to do so but after this, I am NOT going back there as long as she works there. Oh and yes, I asked the other lady to make my sandwich because I didn't want the other one to make me one with attitude.

I had my whole meal made, frantically couldn't find my wallet!!
The owner was SO nice and said to take it and eat and not to worry. However I was able to locate my wallet (at home) and I promised him that I would swing by first thing in the am, he said not to worry. Super nice guy, with a lot of understanding, most owners woulda said your loss. Besides the sandwich was great too today! A bad situation wasn't so bad thanks to him!
Chicken bacon ranch with honey mustard 🤤

If food safety matters to you, then you think very differently from this Subway.

I watched a staff member without a name tag handle customer transactions and receipts, gloves on, then prepare a sandwich with the same gloves. I asked her if she is really going to make a sandwich with cash contaminated gloves, and she actually rolled her eyes at me and kept doing it.

I have never before seen just flagrant and willing disregard for customer safety before in my life, especially on the tail end of a pandemic.

No food service facility should ever allow food to touch a surface that also touches objects given by customers. That is a basic food safety rule. If this is not being followed, I dont even want to know what other safety measures they are not taking.

Unless you want to get sick, please eat somewhere else.

First off, I’ll say I do like this subway! When I can eat in, that is. Only half the staff seems like they have any ounce of customer service left in them, but I’ve worked food service (Subway specifically, at that!), I get it. I never feel too harshly toward tired or annoyed workers unless they make me feel particularly unwanted.
One of the positives is that they’re generous with their veggies. I love olives on my subway sandwiches, and I always feel out of place asking for more, but they pile them on without hesitation, which is GREAT.
But buyer beware if you try to order from them through a delivery service like Uber eats or Grubhub. It’s a 50/50 chance that the order will even be accepted, let alone completed. Half the times we’ve ordered, they’ve not confirmed it, so it automatically gets cancelled. I get it, it can get busy, especially during the dinner hours. But half the times we’ve ordered?
Tonight takes the cake. The order was accepted, but Uber was having trouble finding a driver that would actually get to the restaurant, so one would be selected and drive closer for a bit, then the delivery driver would switch. Finally, after 3 drivers fail to get there, the fourth one makes it to the restaurant with 10 minutes to spare before the Subway closes. At this point it’s been nearly an hour since the order was accepted. Ample time to make two sandwiches and grab a Gatorade from the cooler. Sure, they’d be a bit cold, but it’s fine. Suddenly, after the driver has been at the restaurant for at least 5 minutes, Subway cancels the order. No communication, just cancels.
When things like this happen, once or twice, it’s easy to think, “maybe there’s a rush. I don’t blame them.”
When it’s happened at least seven times, it feels almost like they just don’t feel like doing their job.

I just love their sauces, signature waffle fries and popcorn chicken nuggets! It doesn't get more simple and delicious than that. Also, I've never had a bad meal no matter the franchise visited. Moderately priced for the flavor and service. Kid friendly and approved family favorite!

I always find it interesting that there service and food is always consistent and am always happy to dine here real quick. Never had a problem...

The flower on the  table is always a nice touch, the place is extremely clean, and everything is just well organized. Every other fast food place should copy this system.

This is how I received my breakfast burrito this morning. Very disappointed! I did curbside, got my order drove off immediately to make it work on time. Arrived at work to see this when I unwrapped my burrito. I've never received quality this bad at a Chick-fil-A. I think I will avoid this location from now on.

We had a gentleman named Robert and a female employee a plus sized associate with short hair with red highlights deny us a manager and confront us. Didn’t give us professional service. I felt I was treated like a “homeless person” because of my unique style. When asked “for here or to go” the tone is something I heard before but it’s not okay I will keep reporting it. And sooner or later these people have to realize they’re actions are not okay.

I order curbside, like the location, and wish they had more space. Their service is impeccable.

I love it when they hand over the goods, I say thank you, and the Chick-fil-A staff member's go-to response is "my pleasure."❤

I used to love coming to this location but today one of the workers, lets call her worker A, was rushing worker B who was attending me. I asked for specific i instructions  because of dietary needs but worker A said they cannot accommodate as more guests were walking in. I was close to being done with my order and she was not the one attending me. She came over and began to make the rest of my order in a rude way. When i asked for more she gave attitude and slammed it on the sandwich, barely put toppings on it and sent me on my way. I’m only giving it a two star rating even though I want to give it a one or zero because worker B was very nice and stayed calm through the whole situation, which helped me not make it a bigger deal but I am highly disappointed.

Went here after work, needed to use the restroom before buying my food. This older Hispanic lady who has a bitter appearance with the worst customer service I’ve seen, said that I needed to buy if I wanted to use their restroom. Of course I was there to purchase a sandwich but didn't want to take inside the restroom and I explained her that in SPANISH!!! Really this place need new people to work here.

If I could give this place no stars I would. Went there on a Sunday August 7th near closing time and the two older Hispanic ladies were there they had the worst customer service I’ve seen. They were more worried about making they’re food to take home than making our food!!!! I told a lady the toppings I wanted and when I noticed she was already closing my sub without adding anything because she was trying to make her sub. This was horrible they were just telling each other to make they’re food in front of us and not giving us proper customer service. Will not be coming back to this location ever. Rather drive a longer distance than come here. Just terrible
eat subway everyday all over southern MD, this is by far one of the best. great portions they actually give you your sub the way you want it. great place highly recommend.

The young lady Johanna did a wonderful job, and was really nice and kind. But the other older women was very rude. When we asked for a napkin for a party of 5 she only gave us two napkins. What a bad service.
Great brews rotates very frequently. Deli sandwiches are amazing! We met a great group of people and hung out for a while!
Best sandwich I have had in a long time. I would put it on par with Publix. (if you know what I mean then you gotta just go).

This place is great! Since I'm new to craft beersI asked for assistance. They were more than willing  and I really the recommendation (furious george). I decided to order sandwiches. I had been staring at the special on the board, found it intriguing,  and decided to order it, Tim's deli sandwich. Best decision I could've made. This sandwich is AMAZING!! I felt like there was a party in my mouth and I didn't want it to end!! Do yourself a favor and try it. You won't regret it...I GUARANTEE!!

The Chief sandwich was so good that I would cross state lines for it they also have some great ANXO cider with is outside of this world. All that is presented with an outstanding service. Thank you so much y’all!

The best Tuna Salad i ever had. Also the staffs are very nice.  Cannot believe i have been avoiding this place for so long.  Also for the wine and beer selections are unbelievable for real. I highly recommend this place any day.

This Papa Johns always does a great job.  Pizza is made well and the app makes it super easy.  I love the ability to order well ahead of time and pick up when it is convenient for me.  Parking lot has plenty of spaces so getting in and out is easy.  Overall, highly recommend it. Note - we do take out.  I would not go there if I am looking for sit-down dining.

Beverage and sauce weren't delivered. When I called to follow up, Maddie said it was because their driver wasn't feeling well at the time of the delivery. What the heck!? And this Maddie doesn't know what customer service is - she keeps putting me on hold without warning. Very unsatisfied customer here.
We ordered pizzas to be delivered at noon, but we ended up call them why not delivered. They said it will 15 minutes late. They never bother to inform us about the delay.
I want to give this place a 5 star.  No only because the storefront was amazing. The general manger really had the best hospitality I ever encountered.
Never had an order wrong, but they always seem to be understaffed.  The low reviews here seem to reflect that, and not any fault of the employees trying to keep up with orders.

Going El Patio is like you’re traveling to Argentina without leaving DC. The food and vibe is incomparable! Not only the food is amazing but the wine and deli shop in the restaurant is nostalgic according to my Argentinian friend. The meat on the grill (Parrillada) for two can actually feed the whole family (4ppl). We definitely had a food coma after the dinner.

We got the steak with chimichurri sauce, a handful of empanadas, and the flan. All of it was good! The corn empanadas reminded me of my Argentinian Grandmother's empanadas con corn. Would highly recommend asking for extra chimichurri sauce, it was the highlight of our meal. We forgot to take photos before starting to eat, the steak wasn't that small ;)

I’m extremely disappointed of this place. I have been coming to this restaurant for years. Every weekend with my wife to be more specific. I used to love this place. However this is the 3rd that we experienced something wrong with the food and horrible costumer service. I love to give good reviews to good restaurants. However we come all the way from Fairfax each weekend and it’s not okay to receive this treatment. The first time that we received our food, I asked for light pasta sauce for my daughter who is only 8.  They brought pasta sauce with extra wine. It was very strong that I couldn’t even eat it myself. I asked to please exchange the pasta. The manager sarcastically responded. “Do you want me to bring you all the sauces for you to taste?” He had such an ugly tone and attitude. We felt very uncomfortable.
We came back a few weeks later. The second time, I found a hair on my steak. I mentioned it to them and they told me they could remove the plate. They discounted half of the plate with an attitude again. Today 3/5/2023 We decided to give it a try. We had just gotten our food and as I’m talking to my wife, I noticed her pulling out a piece of cleaning kitchen SPONGE out her mouth. We couldn’t believe our eyes. The  manager came over and said “oh sometimes we washed  our plates with metal and plastic sponges and it was probably a piece left. They did not do anything. He said it was probably a mistake.
I am a restaurant manager/ chef. I make sure all my employees watch and sanitize all kitchen utensils and plates. There should’ve never been hair, or cleaning sponges in the food. That is no unsanitary. And what makes me extremely upset is the fact that they don’t even offer an apology  or a solution to provide the best costumer service. This is not how you take care to costumers. As a guest I shouldn’t have to see this kind of stuff in my lunch plate. I’m very disappointing of them and Manager of how she handled this situation. At the end she offered us a new portion of fries or a free dessert. We   would not be returning because of their unprofessionalism. We hated to spend 100+ each week just to come here and always find something and feel horribly unpleasant.

Asado, or BBQ, is a ritualistic rite of passage for many Argentinians, not just a meal, but a ritual experience not done by everyone, but the most knowledgeable barbecuer. El patio brings that to Rockville. The most common cuts of meat like flank, NY strip, with the not so common cuts like Mollejas (gizzard; chicken organ),  chinchulines (beef small intestine), all in a platter for you to figure out where to start first. The meat is prepared exactly to your preferred temperature; Paired with their house wines at 5 dollars a glass Pinot Noir, Malbec, or whites, you know you are in for a treat. Start with empanadas either baked or fried. You are in for not just a meal, but a rite of passage of what Argentinians call, Asado. If you are curious about Asado, check out Netflix's satirical documentary, "Todo sobre el Asado". You'll love it.

Also, it goes without saying, I wouldn't recommend this place to my vegan friends.

We have been dining at El Patio for years and they never disappoint. Guillermo and Co. have continued to be passionate about their offerings and focused on customer service even after many years of excellence. Continuity is paramount in this business and you will find the same delicious quality time after time. This is a rarity in the restaurant world where burnout often occurs. No one does steak better and the wine offerings are very good as well. Vegetarian? No problem, the spinach cannelloni  is amazing and there are corn, spinach and cheese and onion empanadas. Servers are generally charming and attentive. This is a neighborhood gem of a restaurant. On July 1st, we had El Patio cater our wedding rehearsal dinner for 80 people. Everything we love about the restaurant was brought to our venue seamlessly: the delicious food, the amazing staff and a good dose of charm as well. These guys are consummate professionals and compliments from guests keep coming even weeks after the event.  We

Not so fresh tasting Thai, our order tasted like it was prepped yesterday and simply reheated today. Portions were oddly small and unevenly flavored.

Our Beef Mussaman was the best of the three dishes and sadly this entree had the smallest broth portion. Flavoring was controlled without anything being overpowering. The beef was indeed soft and the two potato chunks were just right.

Our green curry was way too spicy (we asked for a two out of five) and we lost every other flavor of the dish after the first bite.

The Tom Ke Hed soup had way too much fish sauce in the broth and the vegetables tasted like they were a day or two short of their expiration date. Again, the portion was very small.

Thankfully our dinner arrived warm so we got a fair expectation of what the meal should taste like.
This is really good. If you go on a weeknight there's no wait. We got the pad Thai and panang curry which was really good. The curry was really coconut heavy. Highly recommend

The food is consistently delicious. We go for the Pad Thai but have liked Ginger Perfect, and Siamese Beef. Guys, this place delivers always. My family and I have been coming here for years. Consistently delicious. What can I say!

It's not a restaurant. It's a diner. Table surfaces are sticky. Boxes are dumped in the back of the dining hall. Price/quality is high. You either decrease prices or increase quality. The soup was way sour, yet, nothing says about it on the menu. Thai iced coffee and some noodles were good. If I were an owner I would entirely renovate this business and change the chef.
Soup was tasty and fresh. No coconut juice in stock. Coconut custard pie rubbery. Calamari appetizer inedible and sent back. Shrimp cakes were likely frozen. Would not return. Very disappointed.

name: Taipei Tokyo Cafe
vicinity: Metro Pike Shopping Center, 11510 Rockville Pike, Rockville

reviews.text: Great place for tasty Asian food and friendly service. We went on a weekday for dinner and Flora really took care of us. She is very friendly and makes you feel at home as soon as you walk in. The recommendations were excellent so here we go. We started some good hot and sour soup followed by some delicious avocado salad, seaweed salad, chicken lettuce wraps and dumplings. Then we had the crispy beef with some Korean fried rice. Both were absolutely delicious. To top it all they brought some perfectly fried spring rolls. Great first visit and looking forward to coming back soon.

Absolutely incredible food & very kind staff. Flora took incredible care of us. Came here twice in one weekend after we were in town for Small Press Expo, and when we're back in the area, we 100% will come back. Tried both the sushi burrito & the poke bowl and both were top notch quality for a really good price. The restaurant itself is very pleasant (tons of natural light if you come during the day) & the tables are spaced out nicely so we felt confident and safe eating here.

Have gotten takeout multiple times from here and every time it’s amazing! Recently ordered a large order for my coworkers and got free edamame and seaweed salad as well! The seafood hotpot was enormous! Big enough for 4-5 people! I usually get sushi, but sushi is just a side gig for them (but still really great!), their specials are unique, most things I haven’t seen before but it’s so good!

We looked for a spot to introduce the kids to some new cuisine and we were so lucky to come across this place. We found everyone to be so friendly and accommodating, the staff was exceptional. Flora took care of us and made everyone feel welcomed. As a total surprise I really enjoyed the vegetable lettuce wraps, even though I'm primarily a carnivore it was so flavorful I couldn't resist. The kids ultimately were brave enough to try some different rolls and  we didn't break the bank to have an awesome family night out. There might be gourmet places in the DC area, but you won't find genuine kindness Iike this very often, we will be back!

Really friendly waitstaff.  Food came out fast hot and fresh.  White rice was excellent!  It’s a busy place eating in and takeout.  While I was there I did observe an unruly customer that was very demanding and rude to the staff.  The staff handled the situation very well with professionalism and respect.  Kudos to this hardworking kind staff.

The lady who gave me my food was very nice. The food was fresh, despite me getting there right before they closed.  This is one of the few suburban McDonald's locations I've seen that doesn't have a drive-thru.

Beware - this is a very poorly operated McDonalds location. I have ordered Curbside pickup at this location several times. At least half of the orders I’ve placed have been incorrectly fulfilled. There’s very little attention to detail paid to customer requests. Furthermore, the quality of the food is often not fresh/hot and the wait times for my orders to be fulfilled have taken as long as 10+ minutes. It’s not a fast food restaurant — it’s “slow” food! SAD!!

This place is so weird. First of all. I don’t understand why a man was in the woman’s bathroom. Thank god he left so I could use the bathroom. I had my points stolen on my app. My whole account got switched to my daughter name. Email stated that she downloaded my McDonald’s app. I knew this was a lie cause my day don’t eat McDonald’s. I asked her & she said she didn’t download no app on her phone. I be like who hired these people. I swear times have truly changed. Smh.

The mobile pick up parking spots have had the numbers painted over.  Otherwise it's a McDonald's, you expect it to be trashy and mess up your order every couple of times.  This store does not disappoint.  Would not recommend if you want quality.  But if you want cheap quick food it's OK.  The food tasted dirty and my double quarter pounder was a single.  That's at least three times in a row that the food was bad.

The hours on Friday are not correct.  They close at midnight on Thursday and open at 6am going into Saturday.

The best way to get a fresh egg McMullen  order it with no cheese, they have to make it new. When the drive up person says pull up to the wait spot say, no thank you I will wait here. They can't say no because of the customer is always right policy and you will get your fresh sandwich double quick.

The guy at the counter seemed very unhappy and unpleasant.  There were very few people in the store.  My order was wrong and I didn't get a receipt.  The BLT had nothing on it, see the photo.  My Dave's Tripple was missing, the fries were cold, and the root beer tasted like dr pepper.

The service here is ALWAYS slow, but today was a bit ridiculous!!!! I counted 7 employees, included the young man Joshua who was on the register. Poor Joshua was left to take AND run his own orders with a line wrapped around in the store while a lady stood by the fry station and another lady and a gentlemen was just standing in the back. I'm highly disappointed. There's NO WAY I could stand there and watch a fellow employee run around like a chicken with their head cut off. Even the manager wasn't stepping in to help Joshua smh they need to DO BETTER! Including the manager!

Classic Wendy's burgers with quick drive thru service. Friendly employees. The drive thru person was a bit hard to understand but got it right and fast.
Get a frosty with fries, thank me later. Salty, sweet, hot and cold.
Dave's double with extra pickles and a Coca Cola were very satisfying.

Bathroom is filthy, smelly, and rundown. It needs a full remodel. I have never seen a bathroom look this bad from a fast food joint. Makes you think what the kitchen looks like. I would avoid from eating here.

This store is disgusting, they reuse food for other customers. They use burned burgers and frozen grill chicken. A lot of cross contamination with frozen chicken and fresh beef. Tons of fruit flies, managers are lazy and incompetent, employees are always on their phones and very rude to customers. I’ve both been serviced there and worked their and I would just love to see the store shut down it’s poorly managed and very disgusting I was sick of having to work there and give customers terrible food. I’ve even seen customers being rung up wrong with no real explanation this store gives Wendy’s a bad name and I hope someone in the top brass sees this and effects big changes because my overall experience there will never make me a customer again.

The staff was great - but the food was absolutely disgusting. The pizza (I ordered a dinner box and 2 medium pizzas) had a strange flavor. I am not sure what the off putting flavor was - it could have been the cheese or the dough itself. I had to throw away my whole Super Bowl dinner.

It’s a shame that I had to give 2 starts to this location. The location need help with customer service. The older lady is always nice and inviting; however one of the younger worker was not professional at all. I was suppose to pick up an order, they gave me some else order by mistake. Had to drive back there to get the right food. The younger lady was not even able to apologies for the mistake. She replied by saying that I should have seen that it wasn’t the right order. While conversing she never apologies for the error that was made and almost blamed me for not seeing that the order wasn’t right! Beside all that, the location is clean and easy to be found.
Great place. Food made fresh! Ample parking. The most excellent customer service: pleasant, helpful. Would be a great restaurant. Only provides carry-out.
Pizza was hot and made the way I ordered it.  The driver didn't get lost, and I tipped him $20.

The new Detroit style pizza is legit. The crust is a little thick, but the edges are crunchy and yummy. The sauce is tasty as well, a hint of sweet but not overwhelming. I expected the cupped pepperoni to be be well, burnt, taste funky. They did look a little burnt but they were tasty. Cheese was there, and ties it all together. Good job Pizza Hut. Totally recommend this new item.

Very poor service, its Friday night 6:30, there is one guy at the counter, 2 others are hanging around. Manager is talking to the guys who are not working, been more than 15 minutes, there are more than 10-12 people waiting.

Chicken overcooked and hard to chew.  I've had good Popeyes chicken breast at other locations that was soft and juicy.
This location needs to review cooking procedures.  Don't want to hurt the brand with a bad experience,  right?

Service was good, the place was clean enough, but the food was disappointing. I have been living outside the US for some years and the quality of the Popeyes food abroad seems much higher than in the he US. Maybe is the oil used or the fact that the food waits a long time under heat lamps. Whatever it is, I have had much better tasting Popeyes outside of the country.

Only received 1 chicken breast piece in a 10 piece order that includes 2 chicken breasts.  This has happened to me twice at this location.  I don't really understand why the workers feel the need to not put 2 chicken breasts in the order when it is supposed to have 2 chicken breast pieces, the biggest piece.
Great location for this chain . open area from the door to the counter dual condiment\soda bar to go along with two sided seating.

Our waitress Michelle was great!  Very friendly and personable. Typically food at any OPH is great and this location doesn’t disappoint. Always a treat. Go early, avoid the crowds. We got there on a Sunday at 7am, empty.

Came this morning with family was disappointed in the service and the food. We all ordered coffee my cup was had a lipstick stain had to wait 20 minutes before our waiter came to take our order. When ordering I asked for over medium eggs got over medium well instead. When ordering my dad food I told the waiter I wanted over hard fried eggs he gave me a werid look. The French tastes like bread cover with eggs. The menu said all 3 meals came with 3 pieces of bacon we got two.the diced potatoes didnt taste right sister couldn't  eat them . The pancakes and French look like they were made for a child 😑.

7/5/2022

Alissa was nice and made good suggestions. We did pay over $100 for 5 people for pancakes and eggs but it was all tasty. Blubbery pancakes, yummy. Wife liked the Dutch baby better with fruit.

On my Middle Class Monotony (MCM) scale (0-5 where 0 is NOT cheap or monotonous and 5 being very cheap and monotonous):

It's easy to get in but not exactly cheap, I'll go with 4 MCM.

This is The place for pancakes. They are absolutely delicious. Staff was friendly and attentive. It’s fairly crowded for lunch but we still got our food in a timely manner. The A/C must be set on high since we and other guests were freezing. We had to ask several times for them to lower the air conditioning. Overall, the pancakes were amazing!

Very disappointed in today's visit.  I LOVED this place the first couple times I went.  Today, I called in my order and was told 20 minutes.  I showed up 35 minutes later and they never even processed the order because of a "printer" problem.  I was told it would be 10 minutes more.  I waited another 20 minutes to get the food.  When I got to my office, I found that the food that took an hour to get was bland and soooo disappointing. The omelettes that used to be fluffy and huge is now deflated and tasteless.  My omelette was missing the cheese and the hash browns were undercooked too.  I was given a small gift card for having to wait so long, but honestly, I'm not sure I'd waste my time to go back.  :(
Amazing experience as it always has been. For 30 years this has been our spot,I have been coming here since childhood. The food, people and atmosphere is why we always come back!

Really loved this place before they sold it. We ordered here as soon as they opened back up under new ownership hopefully to get the same great taste.

But unfortunately the pizza was burnt, no bread came with the meal, our banana crème dessert tasted like they used old milk and my crab pasta barely had any crab in it.

I gave then an opportunity to fix it, but a few empty messages and no real refund or fix.

What a fun surprise of a restaurant! It's in the most unassuming area surrounding by industrial type buildings and not noticeable. It's definitely got an old-world Italian restaurant feel. Service was nice and quick enough. The food was surprisingly good. Burrata special and fresh mozzarella and tomatoes were both delicious. The salad with goat cheese was also great. Rigatoni with meatballs was good, and rigatoni with bolognese was phenomenal. The grilled branzino was also excellent. Chianti was a nice choice. The limoncello mascarpone cake was truly something special. Light, moist, perfectly balanced. We highly recommend it! Parking is ok, but limited. Family friendly.

Been eating here since I was a kid. The WHITE PIZZA is incredible. For dessert the cannoli is wonderful. Large portions so I can have lunch the next day. My only complaint is I live an hour away and can't eat here as often as I'd like

Long time Amalfi’s fans, first time Chef Tony’s visitors, and overall we found the food really awful unfortunately. We went in understanding that the menu had become much more seafood oriented than Italian and were excited to simply get a white pizza and try some of the new establishments options. The white pizza came out doughy and undercooked (we’ve always had to fight over the last slice with our family, this time we took much of it home and ended up throwing it away). Two of us ordered pasta, one ordered a meat, and one ordered a fish. None of us were impressed, and we tasted each others dishes (begrudgingly afterwords..) and concurred. I’m not going to say it’s the worst meal I’ve ever had like the last reviewer, but it was certainly one of the most sub par meals I’ve had at any restaurant in recent memory. The staff was very nice and eager to please albeit a bit frazzled (which we get, they are still a new place). But the food was not something I could see myself returning for even if it was a free meal. That said, giving the place three stars because I think it’s unfair to totally decimate the reviews this early in the operation of any place, and because the staff was friendly. But if you are thinking about going to capture part of the Amalfi’s vibe or menu, I’d suggest either giving them a lot more time to figure things out or just not going,.. it was not good at all and was honestly a one star experience.
